data.text: @greg_manthey @qldhealth Go for it, maybe they can explain data accuracy and caveats to you.

@greg_manthey @qldhealth Do you know what lag means? I means a delay in throughput. As in, 3000 cases are reported, their data accuracy process manages to process 1000, they update the number by 1000 as that is all the process has approved.

Your incredulity is astounding.
@erob_po @qldhealth If this keeps up I will be informing the Australian Government Department of Health

@erob_po @qldhealth 11,549 cases from the last 4 days have not been added to the TOTAL number of cases recorded. No other state has this big a discrepancy. What are you trying to pull QLD health?
https://t.co/otxpB8YTe9

@erob_po @qldhealth A lag in cases you say. From when and I why is it always less? As for data caveat as you say, I think perhaps you need to research what a caveat is, not me!
Today there was 3,677 new cases but only 1,592 were added to the TOTAL cases. What happened to the 2,085 cases? Vanished?

@greg_manthey @qldhealth Yep, there a data lag. Says there could be a data lag in the caveats. 

You not understanding what a data caveat is, when they’re right there on the page you’re quoting numbers from is an indictment on you, not on QLD health.

@greg_manthey @qldhealth Got any evidence the data caveats have nothing to do with data being slow to update?

Or just making shit up?
@erob_po @qldhealth This has nothing to do with Caveats, stop being dumb!

@erob_po @qldhealth QLD's TOTAL number of cases recorded increased by 265 today yet the number of new cases recorded today was 2,934.
Even a primary school child could see something is wrong there!
